law.text:
The cabinet shall:
Administer all funds appropriated to implement the provisions of KRS 200.650 to 200.676;
Identify and coordinate all available financial resources for early intervention within the Commonwealth from federal, state, local, and private sources, including but not limited to:
Title V of the Federal Social Security Act relating to maternal and child health;
Title XIX of the Federal Social Security Act relating to Medicaid and the Early Periodic Screening Diagnostic and Treatment (EPSDT) program;
The Federal Head Start Act;
The Federal Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, Parts B and H;
The Federal Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1964 Title I, Chapter I, Part B, Subpart 2 as amended;
The Federal Developmentally Disabled Assistance and Bill of Rights Act, P.L. 100-146;
Other federal programs; and
Private insurance.
Develop a sliding fee scale of the cost of early intervention services to families, including those circumstances where no fee shall be required;
Make available, in addition to the services specified in KRS 200.654(7), social skill development and behavioral therapy services to infants and toddlers with a diagnosis of pervasive developmental disorders;
Enter into contracts with service providers within a local community aided by the district committee in identifying providers;
Develop procedures to monitor and evaluate services that are provided to infants and toddlers with disabilities and their families;
Develop procedures to ensure that early intervention services identified on the individualized family service plan are provided to eligible infants and toddlers with disabilities and their families in a timely manner pending resolution of any disputes among public agencies or service providers; and
In conjunction with the council and district early intervention committees, promulgate administrative regulations, pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A, necessary to implement the provisions of KRS 200.650 to 200.676.
